penner-up
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:a person responsible for filling pens with sheep during drafting, docking, drenching, foot-rotting or shearing; also used at freezing works.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
